# NEWS
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------
# What: What are the news for GeneticsPed?
# Time-stamp: <2007-04-03 16:08:08 ggorjan>
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 0.1.2
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

o Now we are more rigorous for value of ascendantSex argument in
  Pedigree(). It must accord to values in sex column, if that one is passed
  of course. [2007-04-01]

o MASS added to depends due to use of fractions() in many places in
  documnetation. [2007-04-01]

o Added vignette on quantitative genetic (animal) model and
  model.matrix.Pedigree() functions for educational purposes. [2007-03-31]

o Created data directory and added pedigree example Mrode2.1 and
  Mrode3.1. [2007-03-31]

o Added unit tests for genetic relationship matrices that should test all
  related functions - mainly against Mrode's book examples -
  runit.genRelMatrix.R. [2007-03-31]

o Added arguments sort and names to inverseAdditive(), relationshipAdditive()
  and inbreeding(). [2007-03-31]

o Reworked core for relationshipAdditive() into vectorized form. [2007-03-30]

o Added geneFlowT(), geneFlowTinv(), geneFlowM() and mendelianSamplingD()
  functions. [2007-03-30/31]

o Registration of native routines - src/register.cc. [2007-03-02]

o Added gpi() function. [2007-03-02]

# 0.1.1
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

o Temporarily removed unknown funcs, due to planned move to BioC and change
  to S4.

o All depends are now in gdata --> removing ggmisc.

# 2006-03-29
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

o codeUnit to get internal codes for subject and ascendants if factors are
  used

o Handled unused levels in nlevels.pedigree and summary.pedigree now
  produces a simple summary

o Started to implement checks in check.pedigree and friends

o Proper factor handling

# 2006-03-16
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

o Playing around with NA/unknown representation - it is very likely that I
  messed up some things with factors --> subject to changes.

# Version 0.1
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------

o Initial version

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEWS ends here
